Paper: hep-th/0101028

Date: 2001-01-04

Title: Holographic Renormalization Group and Fermionic Boundary Data

Authors: Jussi Kalkkinen, Dario Martelli

Comments: 7 pages, LaTeX, contribution to the proceedings of the RTN-workshop

"The Quantum Structure of Spacetime and the Geometric Nature of FundamentalInteractions," Berlin, October 2000Journal-ref: Fortsch.Phys. 49 (2001) 565-571

We discuss Holographic Renormalization Group equations in the presence offermions and form fields in the bulk. The existence of a holographically dualquantum field theory for a given bulk gravity theory imposes consistencyconditions on the ranks of the form fields, the fermion - form field couplings,and leads to a novel Ward identity.